It is a financial control methodology where all monthly income (tax deducted) is distributed to 5 different destinations. They are Essential Expenses (55%), Leisure (10%), Education (10%), Short/Medium Term Goals (10%) and, finally, Financial Freedom (15%).

Essential Expenses (55% of total income)
55% of all your income should be used for your essential expenses. Essential Expenses are all those indispensable for your life. As an example, we can mention the costs of food, housing, transportation, day-to-day bills, credit card bills, children's school fees, etc. If any expense is essential for your life, it must be included within your essential expenses.

Leisure (10% of total income)
It is recommended that you spend 10% of your monthly income on leisure activities. Leisure expenses include any expenses that are extra to essential expenses that bring you joy and happiness. This part of your budget is carte blanche to spend on anything that isn't essential but that you enjoy purchasing or consuming.

Education (10% of total income)
